Miklós Szabados.label: Miklós Szabados
Miklós Szabados.description: Miklós Szabados was a Hungarian and Australian table tennis champion. Wikipedia

Kjell Johansson (table tennis).label: Kjell Johansson
Kjell Johansson (table tennis).description:
Kjell Johansson was a male former table tennis player from Sweden.
From 1963 to 1977 he won several medals in singles, doubles, and team events in the European Table Tennis Championships and in the World Table Tennis Championships. Wikipedia

Elizabeta Samara.label: Elizabeta Samara
Elizabeta Samara.description: Elizabeta Samara, is a Romanian professional table tennis and a three-time European champion. She is currently the player of Fenerbahçe SK. Wikipedia

Andrzej Grubba.label: Andrzej Grubba
Andrzej Grubba.description:
Andrzej Grubba was a Polish table tennis player.
Grubba was born in Brzeźno Wielkie near Starogard Gdański. He was the recipient of numerous medals for the world competition in table tennis as well as for the European competition. Wikipedia

Erik Lindh.label: Erik Lindh
Erik Lindh.description:
Erik Lindh is a former international Swedish table tennis player who competed in the 1988 Summer Olympics and in the 1992 Summer Olympics.
In the 1988 Summer Olympics in Seoul he finished in third place and won the bronze medal. Wikipedia

Finn Tugwell.label: Finn Tugwell
Finn Tugwell.description: Finn Tugwell is a Danish table tennis professional. He pairs up with Danish Michael Maze in doubles, with whom he won the bronze medal at the 2004 Summer Olympics, beating the Russian pair Dmitry Mazunov/Alexey Smirnov. Wikipedia

Michael Maze.label: Michael Maze
Michael Maze.description: Michael Maze is a table tennis player from Faxe, Denmark. He normally plays both in the men's singles and in men's doubles. As of 2005, he is one of the top five left-handed players in the world. Wikipedia

Hans Alsér.label: Hans Alsér
Hans Alsér.description:
Hans Alsér was a Swedish table tennis player and later the head coach of West German and Swedish national teams. His nickname, Hasse, was often used in media.
Hans Alsér was an international top level player. Wikipedia

Ulf \"Tickan\" Carlsson.label: Ulf "Tickan" Carlsson
Ulf \"Tickan\" Carlsson.description: Ulf "Tickan" Carlsson is a Swedish table tennis player, active at international level during the 1980s. His best achievement was gold at the 1985 World Championships. Wikipedia

Buddy Blattner.label: Buddy Blattner
Buddy Blattner.description: Robert Garnett Blattner, commonly known as "Buddy" or "Bud" Blattner, was an American table tennis and baseball player and radio and television sportscaster. Wikipedia
Buddy Blattner.Born: February 8, 1920, St. Louis, Missouri, United States

Jun Mizutani.label: Jun Mizutani
Jun Mizutani.description: Jun Mizutani is a male Japanese table tennis player. He became the youngest Japanese national champion at the age of 17. Wikipedia

Kasumi Ishikawa.label: Kasumi Ishikawa
Kasumi Ishikawa.description: Kasumi Ishikawa is a female Japanese table tennis player. Her entire family, which consists of her father, mother, and younger sister, play table tennis. Wikipedia

Koki Niwa.label: Koki Niwa
Koki Niwa.description: Koki Niwa is a Japanese male table tennis player. He is the gold medalist at the 2010 Youth Olympic Games and he won the World Junior Table Tennis Championships in 2010 and 2011. He is currently one of the top players under the age of 21. Wikipedia

Ma Wenge.label: Ma Wenge
Ma Wenge.description: Ma Wenge is a male table tennis player from China. He won a bronze medal in 1992 Barcelona Olympics Games in men's single, as well as men's team champion of 1995 and 1997 world table tennis championship. Wikipedia

Natalia Partyka.label: Natalia Partyka
Natalia Partyka.description: Natalia Partyka is a Polish table tennis player. Born without a right hand and forearm, she participates in competitions for able-bodied athletes as well as in competitions for athletes with disabilities. Wikipedia

Vladimir Samsonov.label: Vladimir Samsonov
Vladimir Samsonov.description: Vladimir Samsonov is a Belarusian professional table tennis player, ranked ninth in the world as of October 2011. He is known in China as the "Tai Chi Master" because of his superb all-around style. Wikipedia

Kenta Matsudaira.label: Kenta Matsudaira
Kenta Matsudaira.description: Kenta Matsudaira is a Japanese table tennis player. Winner of 2006 World Junior Championships in boys' singles. He was ranked as the world number one junior player in 2008. Kenta has supposedly one of the world's best serves. Wikipedia

Naomi Yotsumoto.label: Naomi Yotsumoto
Naomi Yotsumoto.description: Naomi Yotsumoto is a female Japanese table tennis player. The style of the self-designed outfits she wears at matches have attracted significant attention from the press. Wikipedia

Pierre-Luc Hinse.label: Pierre-Luc Hinse
Pierre-Luc Hinse.description: Pierre-Luc Hinse also known as "Pete", is a Canadian table tennis player, who is sponsored by DONIC and is, as of May 2012, ranked #311 on the ITTF world ranking, and #5 in Canada. Wikipedia

Stellan Bengtsson.label: Stellan Bengtsson
Stellan Bengtsson.description: Stellan Bengtsson is a former Swedish table tennis player. He won, as first Swede, the singles at the World Table Tennis Championships 1971. He has won numerous medals at international level. Wikipedia

Adrian Crișan.label: Adrian Crișan
Adrian Crișan.description: Adrian Crişan is a Romanian professional table tennis player who currently plays with SV Werder Bremen. He competed in the Summer Olympic Games in 2000, 2004, 2008 and 2012. He is No.20 in the World Rankings as of October, 2012. Wikipedia

Thomas von Scheele.label: Thomas von Scheele
Thomas von Scheele.description: Thomas von Scheele is a left-handed Swedish table tennis player. He won a gold medal in the double event of the World Table Tennis Championships in 1991 with Peter Karlsson. He also won several medals in the European Table Tennis Championships. Wikipedia

Song Ah Sim.label: Song Ah Sim
Song Ah Sim.description: Song Ah Sim is a Chinese table tennis player who competed in the 2000 Summer Olympics and 2004 Summer Olympics for Hong Kong. Wikipedia

Zoltán Berczik.label: Zoltán Berczik
Zoltán Berczik.description: Zoltán Berczik was a Hungarian table tennis player. In the late fifties he was ranked among the best European table tennis players and won, with his athletic play, the first two titles at the Table Tennis European Championships. Wikipedia

Jörgen Persson.label: Jörgen Persson
Jörgen Persson.description: Jörgen Persson is a Swedish table tennis player. In two memorable World Table Tennis Championships finals he faced fellow Swede Jan-Ove Waldner in 1989 and 1991, losing the former and winning the latter. Wikipedia

Patrick Chila.label: Patrick Chila
Patrick Chila.description:
Patrick Chila is a French table tennis player who has competed at five Olympics from 1992 to 2008.
He won a bronze medal with Jean-Philippe Gatien in doubles at the 2000 Olympics. He is also four-time champion of France. Wikipedia

Desmond Douglas.label: Desmond Douglas
Desmond Douglas.description: Desmond Douglas MBE is a British table tennis player, He lived and was brought up in the area of Handsworth, Birmingham, West Midlands. He was an attacking, left-handed, player, notable for his scissor jump smash. Wikipedia

Cao Zhen (table tennis).label: Cao Zhen
Cao Zhen (table tennis).description: Cao Zhen is a Chinese table tennis player. Wikipedia

Fan Ying.label: Fan Ying
Fan Ying.description: Fan Ying is a Chinese table tennis player. Wikipedia

Feng Yalan.label: Feng Yalan
Feng Yalan.description: Feng Yalan is a female Chinese table tennis player. Wikipedia

Liu Shiwen.label: Liu Shiwen
Liu Shiwen.description: Liu Shiwen is a Chinese table tennis player. She was the winner of 2009 and 2012 World Cup, 6 times winner of Pro Tour, winner of 2011 Pro Tour Grand Final and the winner of Asian cup in 2010. Wikipedia

Tang Peng.label: Tang Peng
Tang Peng.description: Tang Peng is a table tennis player from Hong Kong, China. He recently married Tie Yana, another table tennis player representing Hong Kong. Wikipedia

Yu Mengyu.label: Yu Mengyu
Yu Mengyu.description: Yu Mengyu is a Singaporean table tennis player. Wikipedia

Sharath Kamal.label: Sharath Kamal
Sharath Kamal.description: Achanta Sharath Kamal born on 12 July 1982 is a professional table tennis player from Tamil Nadu India. His mother tongue is Telugu. His current world rank is 53rd in the world. Wikipedia

Tamara Boroš.label: Tamara Boroš
Tamara Boroš.description: Tamara Boroš is a female table tennis player competing for Croatia. She has been one of the relatively rare European players who competes at the highest level of the sport together with the players from Far East. Wikipedia

Sky Andrew.label: Sky Andrew
Sky Andrew.description: Skylet Andrew, often known as Sky Andrew, is an English former Olympian who won 3 gold medals at the 1989 Commonwealth Table Tennis Championships and was the first Black British sports agent. Wikipedia
Sky Andrew.Born: March 31, 1962 (age 51), Upton Park, London, United Kingdom

He Zhi Wen.label: He Zhi Wen
He Zhi Wen.description: He Zhiwen, Spanish nickname "Juanito", is a Spanish male table tennis player. He is ranked #41 in the ITTF world ranking. Born in China, his birth name, He Zhiwen, follows Chinese style where He is the family name and Zhiwen is the given name. Wikipedia

Ni Xialian.label: Ni Xialian
Ni Xialian.description:
Ni Xialian is a female Chinese-born table tennis player who now represents Luxembourg. She was born in Shanghai, and resides in Ettelbruck.
She won team and individual gold medals in the 1983 World Table Tennis Championships. Wikipedia

Pradeeban Peter-Paul.label: Pradeeban Peter-Paul
Pradeeban Peter-Paul.description:
Pradeeban Peter-Paul is a Tamil Canadian table tennis player.
Born in Colombo, Sri Lanka, Pradeeban Peter-Paul emigrated with his family to Germany at the age of 11. It was in Würzburg, Germany that Peter-Paul learned table tennis. Wikipedia

Zhang Mo.label: Zhang Mo
Zhang Mo.description:
Zhang Mo is a female Chinese-born table tennis player who now represents Canada.
She competed at the 2008 Summer Olympics, reaching the third round of the singles competition.
She was born in Shijiazhuang, and resides in Ottawa. Wikipedia

Mohammad Reza Akhlaghpasand.label: Mohammad Reza Akhlaghpasand
Mohammad Reza Akhlaghpasand.description: Mohammad Reza Akhlaghpasand also known as Shahin Akhlaghpasand is an Iranian table tennis player. Wikipedia

Aleksandar Karakašević.label: Aleksandar Karakašević
Aleksandar Karakašević.description: Aleksandar Karakašević is a Serbian table tennis player. His incredible feeling and powerful backhand has helped him win against some of the top players in the world. He won a bronze medal on 2011 European Championship. Wikipedia

Ding Ning.label: Ding Ning
Ding Ning.description: Ding Ning is a Chinese table tennis player. She was the winner of women's singles in the 2011 World Table Tennis Championships. Wikipedia

Hao Shuai.label: Hao Shuai
Hao Shuai.description: Hao Shuai is a Chinese table tennis player. Wikipedia

Jiang Huajun.label: Jiang Huajun
Jiang Huajun.description: Jiang Huajun is a table tennis player from Hong Kong, China. Wikipedia

Sun Beibei.label: Sun Beibei
Sun Beibei.description: Sun Beibei is a Singaporean table tennis player. She occupies the 20th place in the ITTF women's world ranking, as of October 2011. Wikipedia

Xu Xin.label: Xin Xu
Xu Xin.description: Xu Xin is a professor at Nanjing University and China's leading Judaic scholar, as well as the founder and director of the Diane and Guilford Glazer Institute for Jewish and Israel Studies at Nanjing University in Nanjing, China. Wikipedia
Books: Legends of the Chinese Jews of Kaifeng

Zhang Jike.label: Zhang Jike
Zhang Jike.description:
Zhang Jike is a Chinese table tennis player. He was named after the Brazilian soccer player Zico.
Zhang Jike is the reigning World and Olympic champion in singles. Wikipedia

Bao Guio Wong Bik Yiu.label: Baguio Wong
Bao Guio Wong Bik Yiu.description: Baguio Wong Bik Yiu is a former female table tennis player from Hong Kong. From 1952 to 1956 she won several medals in singles, doubles, and team events in the Asian Table Tennis Championships. Wikipedia

Cao Yanhua.label: Cao Yanhua
Cao Yanhua.description: Cao Yanhua is a female former table tennis player from China. From 1978 to 1985 she won several medals in singles, doubles, and team events in the Asian Table Tennis Championships and in the World Table Tennis Championships. Wikipedia

Chen Pao-Poe.label: Chen Pao-pei
Chen Pao-Poe.description: Chen Pao-pei is a former female table tennis player from Taiwan. She won several medals in singles, doubles, and team events in the Asian Table Tennis Championships in 1953 and 1957. Wikipedia

Chen Xinhua.label: Chen Xinhua
Chen Xinhua.description: Chen Xinhua is a male former table tennis player. He is from China, but obtained the English citizenship in 1990. From 1978 to 1992 he won several medals in singles, doubles, and team events in the World Table Tennis Championships. Wikipedia

Daniela Guergueltcheva.label: Daniela Guergueltcheva
Daniela Guergueltcheva.description: Daniela Guergueltcheva is a former female table tennis player from Bulgaria. In 1990 she won two medals in singles and mixed double events in the Table Tennis European Championships. Wikipedia

Fliura Abbate-Bulatova.label: Fliura Abbate-Bulatova
Fliura Abbate-Bulatova.description: Fliura Abbate-Bulatova is a former Soviet and then Italian table tennis player. Her main achievement has been the gold medal in the single competition at the Table Tennis European Championships in 1988. Wikipedia

Gábor Gergely.label: Gábor Gergely
Gábor Gergely.description: Gábor Gergely is a male former table tennis player from Hungary. From 1974 to 1983 he won several medals in singles, doubles, and team events in the Table Tennis European Championships, three medals ... Wikipedia

Hu Yulan.label: Hu Yulan
Hu Yulan.description: Hu Yulan is a former female table tennis player from China. From 1972 to 1975 she won several medals in singles, doubles, and team events in the Asian Table Tennis Championships and in the World Table Tennis Championships. Wikipedia

Ivan Andreadis.label: Ivan Andreadis
Ivan Andreadis.description: Ivan Andreadis was a former Czechoslovak table tennis player. He won several medals in singles, doubles, and team events in the World Table Tennis Championships from 1947 to 1957. Wikipedia

Mirjam Hooman-Kloppenburg.label: Mirjam Hooman-Kloppenburg
Mirjam Hooman-Kloppenburg.description: Mirjam Hooman-Kloppenburg is a former female table tennis player from Netherlands. She won three medals in singles, doubles, and team events in the Table Tennis European Championships at Stuttgart in 1992. Wikipedia

Qianhong Gotsch-He.label: Qianhong Gotsch-He
Qianhong Gotsch-He.description: Qianhong Gotsch-He is a former female table tennis player from Germany. She won two medals in singles, and team events at the Table Tennis European Championships in 2000. She also won several tournaments of the ITTF Pro Tour. Wikipedia

Ruth Aarons.label: Ruth Aarons
Ruth Aarons.description: Ruth Hughes Aarons was a former US table tennis player, vaudeville entertainer, and talent manager. Wikipedia

Shi Zhihao.label: Shi Zhihao
Shi Zhihao.description: Shi Zhihao is a male former table tennis player from China. He won several medals in singles, doubles, and team events at the 1980 Asian Table Tennis Championships. Wikipedia

Steffen Fetzner.label: Steffen Fetzner
Steffen Fetzner.description: Steffen Fetzner is a male former table tennis player from Germany. From 1989 to 2000 he won several medals in doubles, and team events in the Table Tennis European Championships, in the World Table ... Wikipedia

Tomie Edano.label: Tomie Edano
Tomie Edano.description: Tomie Edano is a former female table tennis player from Japan. From 1973 to 1976 she won several medals in singles, doubles, and team events in the World Table Tennis Championships and in the Asian Table Tennis Championships. Wikipedia

El-sayed Lashin.label: El-sayed Lashin
El-sayed Lashin.description: El-Sayed Lashin is an Egyptian table tennis player. His current club is Al Ahly in Cairo, where he resides. He qualified for his third Olympic Games at the All Africa Games held in September 2011 in Maputo, Mozambique. Wikipedia

Iveta Vacenovská.label: Iveta Vacenovská
Iveta Vacenovská.description:
Iveta Vacenovská is a Czech Table tennis player. She resides in Linz, Austria and plays for Linz AG Froschberg.
Based on her world ranking in May 2011, she qualified directly for the London 2012 Olympic Games. Wikipedia

Li Nan (table tennis).label: Li Nan
Li Nan (table tennis).description: Li Nan is a female table tennis player from China. From 2000 to 2003 she won several medals in the World Table Tennis Championships and in the Asian Championships. Wikipedia

Liu Song (table tennis).label: Liu Song
Liu Song (table tennis).description: Liu Song is a male table tennis player from Argentina. From 1998 to 2011 he won several medals in singles, doubles, and team events in the Latin American Table Tennis Championships. Wikipedia

Patrick Baum (table tennis).label: Patrick Baum
Patrick Baum (table tennis).description: Patrick Baum is a male table tennis player from Germany. He won the singles title at the 2007 World Junior Table Tennis Championships. Wikipedia

Tvin Carole Moumjoghlian.label: Tvin Carole Moumjoghlian
Tvin Carole Moumjoghlian.description: Tvin Carole Moumjoghlian is a Lebanese table tennis player currently playing for Homenetmen Beirut. With her win at the West Asia Women's Qualification Tournament, she qualified for the London 2012 Olympic Games. Wikipedia

Tiago Apolónia.label: Tiago Apolónia
Tiago Apolónia.description: Tiago Apolónia is a Portuguese table tennis player, who is currently playing for German club TTF LIEBHERR Ochsenhausen. Wikipedia

Adrien Mattenet.label: Adrien Mattenet
Adrien Mattenet.description: Adrien Mattenet is a French table tennis player, currently playing for AS Pontoise-Cergy TT. His World Ranking is at number 19 as of December 2011, the best ranking for a French player since Christophe Legout in 2001. Wikipedia

Gabriel Copola.label: Gabriel Copola
Gabriel Copola.description: Gabriel Copola is an Argentine Wheelchair Table Tennis player with competition Classification 3. He plays for ALENA in Morón, Buenos Aires. Now is a TOPTEN in Class 3. TWgaby_copola FB Gabriel Copola Wikipedia

Hunor Szőcs.label: Hunor Szőcs
Hunor Szőcs.description:
Hunor Szőcs is a Romanian professional table tennis player of Hungarian ethnicity, who plays for the Swiss club TTC Neuhausen.
He became singles champion of Romania in 2012.
Szőcs has a younger sister, Bernadette, who is also a table tennis player. Wikipedia

Liam Pitchford.label: Liam Pitchford
Liam Pitchford.description: Liam Pitchford is a British table tennis player. Wikipedia

Nadeen El-Dawlatly.label: Nadeen El-Dawlatly
Nadeen El-Dawlatly.description: Nadeen El-Dawlatly is an Egyptian table tennis player. She plays for El-Ahly Club in Cairo. She qualified for the London 2012 Olympic Games with her result at the 2011 All-Africa Games. Wikipedia

Noshad Alamian.label: Noshad Alamiyan
Noshad Alamian.description:
Noshad Alamian Darounkolaei is an Iranian table tennis player.
Alamian made a breakthrough at 2008 ITTF World Junior Championships held in Madrid, Spain by beating junior world no. 1 Kenta Matsudaira; despite being coachless he finished 5th overall. Wikipedia

Cem Zeng.label: Cem Zeng
Cem Zeng.description: Cem Zeng; is a male Chinese-born Turkish table tennis player. He has played for Fenerbahçe TT since 2006; he also has played for Quan Xing Si Chuan in China. Wikipedia

Melek Hu.label: Melek Hu
Melek Hu.description: Melek Hu; is a female Chinese-born Turkish table tennis player. She has played for Fenerbahçe TT since 2007 and also played for An Gang in China. Wikipedia

Slobodan Grujić.label: Slobodan Grujić
Slobodan Grujić.description: Slobodan Grujić is a male Serbian table tennis player. He plays for Fenerbahçe TT since 2007 and also played for Novi Sad TT in Serbia and TTV RE-BAU Gönnern in Germany. Wikipedia

Cai Zhenhua.label: Cai Zhenhua
Cai Zhenhua.description: Cai Zhenhua is a male former table tennis player from China. He is the deputy Director of State General Administration of Sports and the presidents of Chinese Football Association, Chinese Badminton Association and Chinese Table Tennis Association. Wikipedia

Anna Sipos.label: Anna Sipos
Anna Sipos.description: Anna Sipos was a Hungarian table tennis player. She won 21 medals in the World Table Tennis Championships. Wikipedia

Georgina Póta.label: Georgina Póta
Georgina Póta.description:
Georgina Póta is a Hungarian table tennis player.
She won gold medal in the team competition at the 2007 Table Tennis European Championships in Belgrade, silver medal in women's doubles and bronze medal in mixed doubles. Wikipedia

Gertrude Pritzi.label: Gertrude Pritzi
Gertrude Pritzi.description: Gertrude Pritzi was a female table tennis player from Austria. From 1937 to 1953 she won several medals in singles, doubles and team events in the World Table Tennis Championships. Wikipedia

Chen Weixing.label: Chen Weixing
Chen Weixing.description:
Chen Weixing is an Austrian table tennis player of Chinese origin. He has played for SVS Lower Austria for several years.
Chen found it difficult to be selected in China's competitive national team. Wikipedia

Johnny Leach.label: Johnny Leach
Johnny Leach.description: Johnny Leach was a British table tennis player. From 1947 to 1955 he won several medals in single, double, and team events at the World Table Tennis Championships, including the individual Men's World ... Wikipedia

Kim Ki-Taik.label: Kim Ki-Taik
Kim Ki-Taik.description:
Kim Ki-Taek is a male former table tennis player from South Korea who competed in the 1988 Summer Olympics.
In 1988 he won the silver medal in the men's singles. Wikipedia

Liu Jia.label: Liu Jia
Liu Jia.description: Liu Jia is a female Chinese-born table tennis player who now represents Austria. Wikipedia

Ichiro Ogimura.label: Ichiro Ogimura
Ichiro Ogimura.description: Ichiro Ogimura was a Japanese table tennis player. Ogimura's father died when he was two and his mother often worked too late to take care of him. As a teenager, Ogimura practiced table tennis at the hall run by Hisae Uehara in Musashino, Tokyo. Wikipedia

Richard Bergmann.label: Richard Bergmann
Richard Bergmann.description: Richard Bergmann was an Austrian and British table tennis player. Winner of seven World Championships, including four Singles, one Men's Doubles, two Team's titles and 22 medals in total. Wikipedia

Li Qian (table tennis).label: Li Qian
Li Qian (table tennis).description: Li Qian is a Chinese-Polish female table tennis player, who currently lives in Tarnobrzeg and represents the team of Siarka Tarnobrzeg. Wikipedia

Shen Yanfei.label: Shen Yanfei
Shen Yanfei.description: Shen Yanfei is a female Chinese-born table tennis player who now represents Spain and resides in Cartagena, Murcia. Her birth name, Shen Yanfei, follows Chinese convention so Shen is the family name and Yanfei the given name. Wikipedia

Wenling Tan Monfardini.label: Wenling Tan Monfardini
Wenling Tan Monfardini.description: Wenling Tan Monfardini is a female Chinese-born professional table tennis player who now represents Italy. Wikipedia

Pär Gerell.label: Pär Gerell
Pär Gerell.description: Pär Håkan Gerell is a Swedish table tennis player. He has been playing for French club Chartres ASTT since 2010. Based on his June 2011 world ranking, Gerell qualified for the London 2012 Olympic Games. Wikipedia

Jens Lundqvist.label: Jens Lundqvist
Jens Lundqvist.description: Jens Lundqvist is a Swedish table tennis player. Wikipedia
